    "body":  "Requested UI Change (No Backend Work):\nReplace the four stacked buttons in the \"Quick Actions\" section of the Dashboard with a grid of 4 visual cards. Each card should include:\n\n- An icon\n- A bold heading\n- A short descriptive subtitle\n- Full card is clickable (links to same location as current button)\n\nCards to Implement:\n\n1. My Qualifications\n\n- Icon: fa-id-badge (or similar)\n- Subtitle: See your current certifications, skills, and qualification status\n- Click Target: Existing route for “View My Qualifications”\n\n2. Manage Team\n\n- Icon: fa-users-cog\n- Subtitle: Assign roles, review staff readiness, track gaps\n- Click Target: Existing route for “Manage Team”\n\n3. Job Roles\n\n- Icon: fa-clipboard-list\n- Subtitle: View available roles and their qualification requirements\n- Click Target: Existing route for “Browse Jobs”\n\n4. Assessments\n\n- Icon: fa-tasks\n- Subtitle: Match team qualifications against job needs\n- Click Target: Existing route for “Review Assessments”\n\nDesign Notes:\n\n- Use a consistent card style (e.g., Bootstrap or Blazor component card)\n- Display as a 2x2 grid if possible for balanced layout\n- Icons can be substituted with equivalents if library is different",
